00:21:42.062 --> 00:21:43.825
Let me just move on.

00:21:43.825 --> 00:21:47.075
I'm hoping that this is in your packet.

00:21:48.695 --> 00:21:51.310
There are two different forms.

00:21:51.310 --> 00:21:54.988
One is for a physician and
one is for an individual

00:21:54.988 --> 00:21:58.655
and/or individual and supporters.

00:22:02.599 --> 00:22:05.266
They are essentially checklists.

00:22:08.908 --> 00:22:10.825
This is a tool that the

00:22:11.869 --> 00:22:16.036
Missouri Center on Excellence
and Disability began,

00:22:17.865 --> 00:22:21.168
and that we have modified
and have been trying out.

00:22:21.168 --> 00:22:23.455
This is version 2.0.

00:22:23.455 --> 00:22:26.427
I expect we'll get to version 16.0

00:22:26.427 --> 00:22:29.010
before we're satisfied with it.

00:22:30.317 --> 00:22:33.150
But I wanted to review it with you

00:22:34.460 --> 00:22:36.724
and ask for your help with this,

00:22:36.724 --> 00:22:40.253
because we want you guys to be the ones

00:22:40.253 --> 00:22:44.420
who are doing the evaluations
for conservatorships.

00:22:45.574 --> 00:22:47.811
You are the ones who work with people

00:22:47.811 --> 00:22:49.736
who have developmental disabilities.

00:22:49.736 --> 00:22:53.569
You understand better
what the capacities are,

00:22:54.742 --> 00:22:56.562
what the potential is.

00:22:56.562 --> 00:22:59.062
You're gonna be less likely to

00:23:00.218 --> 00:23:02.361
default to stereotypes

00:23:02.361 --> 00:23:04.973
about limitations and the need for

00:23:04.973 --> 00:23:07.435
a plenary conservatorship,

00:23:07.435 --> 00:23:10.935
and more likely to identify that there are

00:23:11.815 --> 00:23:13.472
many ways in which people who would

00:23:13.472 --> 00:23:17.121
otherwise be put under conservatorship

00:23:17.121 --> 00:23:20.788
could in fact use
supported decision-making.

00:23:25.442 --> 00:23:30.059
It's very hard to put a
chart up on a PowerPoint,

00:23:30.059 --> 00:23:32.976
but I want to pull this out for you

00:23:36.780 --> 00:23:40.947
to highlight that there are
not yes/no columns here.

00:23:42.137 --> 00:23:44.137
There are three columns.

00:23:45.647 --> 00:23:49.480
On the left hand side
are the various areas...

00:23:51.588 --> 00:23:54.421
Thank you, it's in the book. Good.

00:23:56.167 --> 00:23:58.241
Various categories in which people

00:23:58.241 --> 00:24:01.241
may or may not need support.

00:24:01.241 --> 00:24:03.390
Various categories in which people

00:24:03.390 --> 00:24:07.057
may or may not be able
to act independently.

00:24:10.123 --> 00:24:13.345
One of the ways that we are hoping

00:24:13.345 --> 00:24:15.678
to expand and change the way

00:24:18.994 --> 00:24:23.879
these competency or conservatorship
evaluations are done,

00:24:23.879 --> 00:24:25.879
is to have an individual

00:24:27.950 --> 00:24:30.619
first fill this out for themselves

00:24:30.619 --> 00:24:32.869
with any available support,

00:24:34.769 --> 00:24:38.852
and talk through with
whomever is supporting them

00:24:40.500 --> 00:24:45.104
which areas they are
able to do by themselves.

00:24:45.104 --> 00:24:49.271
Maybe they're able to
communicate very effectively.

00:24:50.694 --> 00:24:54.861
Maybe there is no problem with
them being able to understand

00:24:57.030 --> 00:24:58.863
how they make choices.

00:25:02.521 --> 00:25:07.204
But this moves from
communication, to personal care,

00:25:07.204 --> 00:25:10.287
to staying safe, to home and friends,

00:25:11.983 --> 00:25:16.150
and breaks each of these
areas down into small bits

00:25:17.013 --> 00:25:20.610
so that you can have a conversation

00:25:20.610 --> 00:25:23.110
with the individual about both

00:25:24.384 --> 00:25:26.626
whether they do this by themselves,

00:25:26.626 --> 00:25:30.356
whether they really don't do it at all,

00:25:30.356 --> 00:25:34.568
or whether they might be
able to do it with support.

00:25:34.568 --> 00:25:37.331
And if they could do it with support,

00:25:37.331 --> 00:25:39.414
who that person might be.

00:25:41.503 --> 00:25:43.670
I'm gonna just reemphasize

00:25:44.913 --> 00:25:47.246
that this is a tool that we,

00:25:49.023 --> 00:25:50.106
as attorneys,

00:25:51.455 --> 00:25:55.785
want the courts to begin
to pay attention to.

00:25:55.785 --> 00:25:58.035
This is a tool that we hope

00:25:59.228 --> 00:26:00.645
will develop some

00:26:02.890 --> 00:26:04.557
real life use to you

00:26:06.798 --> 00:26:10.274
and to us when we are working with people

00:26:10.274 --> 00:26:13.235
who may be put under conservatorship,

00:26:13.235 --> 00:26:16.671
or may be eligible for
supported decision-making.

00:26:16.671 --> 00:26:19.588
It's also a tool that can just help

00:26:23.327 --> 00:26:27.009
in facilitating someone's independence.

00:26:27.009 --> 00:26:29.759
It's a way of seeing which skills

00:26:30.678 --> 00:26:34.257
might be able to be increased with support

00:26:34.257 --> 00:26:36.090
and learned over time.

00:26:40.453 --> 00:26:43.635
Let me just give a couple
more examples here.

00:26:43.635 --> 00:26:46.218
For example, in transportation.

00:26:49.097 --> 00:26:51.514
It may be that someone who is

00:26:53.204 --> 00:26:55.204
going regularly to a job

00:26:56.461 --> 00:27:00.222
or to a friend's house or to a store,

00:27:00.222 --> 00:27:02.312
has learned that skill,

00:27:02.312 --> 00:27:04.167
knows which bus to take,

00:27:04.167 --> 00:27:06.777
knows where their Clipper Card is,

00:27:06.777 --> 00:27:09.297
and knows the route or even what to do

00:27:09.297 --> 00:27:13.134
if they miss their stop
and need to go backwards.

00:27:13.134 --> 00:27:17.325
That would be a skill that
is fully independent, right?

00:27:17.325 --> 00:27:20.473
There is no need for support.

00:27:20.473 --> 00:27:22.660
But if they have a doctor's appointment,

00:27:22.660 --> 00:27:23.673
or a specialist's appointment

00:27:23.673 --> 00:27:26.199
that they haven't been to before,

00:27:26.199 --> 00:27:27.366
it may be that

00:27:28.307 --> 00:27:30.713
that is something that they

00:27:30.713 --> 00:27:32.845
could figure out with support.

00:27:32.845 --> 00:27:36.678
Someone reminds them of
the map and the route,

00:27:37.832 --> 00:27:41.297
and talks about that with them beforehand.

00:27:41.297 --> 00:27:43.646
Or it may be that for that one instance,

00:27:43.646 --> 00:27:45.709
they need someone to go with them.

00:27:45.709 --> 00:27:47.790
Or they need someone to order a taxi

00:27:47.790 --> 00:27:50.058
to take them back and forth.

00:27:50.058 --> 00:27:51.864
That's the kind of thing that,

00:27:51.864 --> 00:27:56.031
as you work with in individual
who has a disability,

00:27:56.909 --> 00:27:59.159
you can develop systems for

00:28:00.676 --> 00:28:04.520
and avoid the types of crises that often

00:28:04.520 --> 00:28:06.962
lead people to say, "this
person needs a conservatorship.

00:28:06.962 --> 00:28:10.545
This person can't be
living independently."

00:28:13.245 --> 00:28:15.526
I'm going to reiterate that

00:28:15.526 --> 00:28:16.859
I recognize that

00:28:17.793 --> 00:28:19.710
folks here are prone to

00:28:21.172 --> 00:28:24.132
support independence. Thank you.

00:28:24.132 --> 00:28:26.297
They're prone to support
supported decision-making.

00:28:26.297 --> 00:28:27.130
Thank you.

00:28:28.765 --> 00:28:31.445
But just because that's your bent,

00:28:31.445 --> 00:28:33.647
doesn't mean we don't want you doing

00:28:33.647 --> 00:28:35.945
conservatorship evaluations.

00:28:35.945 --> 00:28:39.347
When we have cases that are brought to us,

00:28:39.347 --> 00:28:42.615
the people who've done the
conservatorship evaluations

00:28:42.615 --> 00:28:44.948
always find that this person

00:28:44.948 --> 00:28:47.241
needs to be under conservatorship.

00:28:47.241 --> 00:28:51.054
We need folks who can present
counter-balancing evidence

00:28:51.054 --> 00:28:55.221
that there are ways in which
this person can function

00:28:56.180 --> 00:29:00.113
and can at least try
supported decision-making

00:29:00.113 --> 00:29:02.863
before we condemn them to what is

00:29:03.910 --> 00:29:06.594
the greatest deprivation
of civil liberties

00:29:06.594 --> 00:29:08.568
aside from the death penalty.

